field.name: DisposableCaps
field.description: Indicates if this container uses interchangeable caps that are disposable; i.e. the cap on the container could be changed to another equivalent cap at any time.

field.name: ContainerMaterials
field.description: The materials of which this container is made that come in direct contact with the samples it contains.

field.name: ImageFile
field.description: A photo of this model of container.

field.name: ImageFileScale
field.description: The scale relating pixels of ImageFile to real world distance.

field.name: Opaque
field.description: Indicates if the exterior of this container blocks the transmission of visible light.

field.name: SelfStanding
field.description: Indicates if this container is capable of staying upright when placed on a flat surface and does not require a rack.

field.name: TransportStable
field.description: Indicates if this container is capable of staying upright without assistance when being transported on an operator cart. Containers that are stable for transport can tolerate cart motion and accidental contact without falling, while those that are not must be resource picked into a rack.

field.name: TareWeight
field.description: The mean weight of empty containers of this model. Experimental tare weights of new containers of this model must be within 5% of this weight.

field.name: TareWeightDistribution
field.description: The statistical distribution of the mean weight of empty containers of this model.

field.name: Resolution
field.description: Resolution of the vessel's volume-indicating markings.

field.name: Graduations
field.description: The markings on this container model used to indicate the fluid's fill level.

field.name: Stocked
field.description: Indicates if the empty containers of this model are kept in stock for use on demand in experiments.

field.name: MinTemperature
field.description: Minimum temperature this type of container can be exposed to and maintain structural integrity.

field.name: MaxTemperature
field.description: Maximum temperature this type of container can be exposed to and maintain structural integrity.

field.name: MinVolume
field.description: The minimum volume required to create a uniform layer at the bottom of the container, indicating the smallest volume needed to reliably aspirate from the container, measure spectral properties, etc.

field.name: MaxVolume
field.description: Maximum volume of fluid the vessel can hold.

field.name: Dimensions
field.description: The external dimensions of this model of container.

field.name: CrossSectionalShape
field.description: The shape of the outside of this container in the X-Y plane.

field.name: Positions
field.description: Spatial definitions of the positions that exist in this model of container, where MaxWidth and MaxDepth are the x and y dimensions of the maximum size of object that will fit in this position. MaxHeight is defined as the maximum height of object that can fit in this position without either encountering a barrier or creating a functional impediment to an experiment procedure.

field.name: AllowedPositions
field.description: Generates a pattern of all the valid position names for this model of container.

field.name: InternalDiameter
field.description: Interior diameter of the vessel's contents holding cavity.

field.name: Aperture
field.description: The minimum opening diameter encountered when aspirating from the container.

field.name: InternalDepth
field.description: The distance from the aperture to the bottom of vessel's contents-holding cavity.

field.name: InternalBottomShape
field.description: Shape of the bottom of the vessel's contents holding cavity.

field.name: Reusability
field.description: Indicates that this container can be used repeatedly.

field.name: DefaultStorageCondition
field.description: The condition in which containers of this model are stored when not in use by an experiment; this condition may be overridden by the specific storage condition of any given container.
